        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/23/2/259/1",
        "text": [
          ": مَنْ کَانَ قِرَاءَتُهُ إِنَّا أَعْطَیْناکَ الْکَوْثَرَ فِی فَرَائِضِهِ وَ نَوَافِلِهِ سَقَاهُ اللَّهُ مِنَ الْکَوْثَرِ یَوْمَ الْقِیَامَهِ وَ کَانَ مُحَدَّثُهُ عِنْدَ رَسُولِ اللَّهِ ص فِی أَصْلِ طُوبَی."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
            "1. From the previous chain from al-Hassan from al-Hussain b. Abi al-’Ala from Abi Basir from Abi Abdillah (a.s.) who said: Whoever recites Surah Kauthar in his obligatory and recommended prayers, Allah would give him to drink from Kauthar on the Day of Judgment and he would be of those who had been with the Messenger of Allah (s.a.w.s.) under the shade of the tree (of Paradise) Tooba."
          ]
        }
      }
